pt had temp 102-103 had trouble keeping down eve of 11DEC93 & 12DEC93; went into convuls & quit breathing eve of 12DEC93 went to hosp dx as result of elevated temp, ear infection & poss react to immun;
severe local react, pos edema, pos tender deltoid; swelling from shoulder to elbow;
pt recvd shot 26OCT93 1 wk later came down flu; fever 101.7, chills, ache;

pt recvd vax lt deltoid; 910AM quarter size raised red area noted around inject site, w/red scattered rash on entire upper arm; c/o tenderness @ site; 915 red area inc to size of half dollar; c/o numbness down lt arm to lt hand;
HISTORY: allergy to birch beer and some perfumes;

SYMPTOM_TEXT: constant crying for 5 hrs but able to feed a little & nap slightly; no fever-had lump on leg for 2 wks;

26OCT93 in eve became pale then started having fussy spells frequently;  mom describes it as flipping out/ (screams, gets red & trembles all over); pediatrician told mom we would decide re giving "P" @ next visit;
p/both immunizations approx 3-4 hrs later had piercing screaming episode that lasted 5 hrs-unconsolable;
approx 1 hr p/vax pt began screaming & this cont until 10PM that evening; pt held by parent & did nap for about 15 mins 2 times; no reddness or fever; given APAP;

pt recvd vax & devel elevated temp w/in 24 hrs p/vax; temp not measured-cont x 1 wk; had high pitched scream, unconsolable, for periods < 3 hrs; occurred periodically 3-4 days; sleeplessness 7-10 days; seen by MD 5OCT93;
dizziness, felt faint, nausea approx 10 mins p/vax; hives devel 45 mins later; pt taken to ER;
HISTORY: previous asthma allergies: Iodine, Codeine, Soap, dust;

SYMPTOM_TEXT: pt recvd vax & started crying p/vax; cried continuously; mom called MD 7PM & was told to use only DT in future; MD did not see pt; pt cried until 10PM until mom got pt to sleep; cry was high pitched;
pt recvd vax 26AUG93, approx 4Pm pt had fever of 105 R; took pt to ER pt admitted for 4 days, fever went up & down r/o UTI;
23OCT severe h/a, migraine-like x 1 day; hematoma @ site of inject; pt has taken flu shot previously; soreness @ site, sore to touch;
17DEC93 brought to ER w/fever & generalized tonic clonic sz;
arthralgias progressive over 2 wks; dec voltage on ECG; echocardiogram pricardial effusion; tx w/Pred;
LAB_DATA: definitively pos ANA, inc ESR-responsing to steroid;

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 2-3d inconsolable crying w/dec sleep & dec breastfeeding & increase in fatigue; adm to hosp 16DEC93 for monitoring;
2 wks p/flu shot, pt developed GBS; in a 46 day hospitalization, the pt required mechanical ventilation, plasmapheresis, 2 endotracheal tubes, 2 vascular catheters, PEG & dobhoff tube;
LAB_DATA: 22OCT CSF: RBC 2, glucose 75, protein 85; urine arsenic, lead, mercury & prophyrins negative; VDRL neg; Crypto neg; CSF fluid for bacteria, fungus, yeast neg;
HISTORY: borderline HTN (untreated); perhaps had Rocky Mountain spotted fever in 1947, no sequelae; NKA;

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 105 fever 21DEC93-seen in hosp ER-no dx;
severe cellulitis distal to inject site in lt deltoid muscle;
5 1/2 hrs p/vax pt had shaking of arms, legs lasting 30 sec; cried out prior "like trembling" had 4-5 episodes; seen in hosp t102 7 was transferred to another hosp for ? of sz;
approx 15 mins p/vax pt exp SOB; began wheezing & was treated w/ventolin; VS otherwise stable; pt then had hives covering arms/legs/abdo; eyes became puffy;
fever reported as t104, measured @ 99; 10 cm area of induration & erythema @ site of Td inject;
Rigidity 4 limbs, eyes rolled back in head; abn breathing, loss of consciousness, lasted 3-4 mins, post ictal drowsiness afterwards (72 hrs p/immun); no treatment given;
8 hrs p/vax pt became fussy w/t102+;
high fever; lethargy x 2 1/2 day; vomiting;
malaise, muscel aches, chest pain;
fever 103, rash diarrhea, weakness, chills, malaise, hives, h/a, muscle aches;
arthralgia 2nd, 3rd MCP joints beginning 6 wks & lasting 8 wks p/last vax;
pruritus over face approx 90 minutes p/vax; gradually subsided over next 30 mins w/o;
onset of sx 5 days post vax; h/a, overall myalgia, lethargic, stomachache & diarrhea;
16NOV93 taken to hosp p/being found by sitter;
mom noticed rapid resp retractions called 911; seized; transported to hosp t104;
approx 48 hrs p/vax mom states pt exhibited uncontrollable, spastic head movements when awake; afebrile; APAP given prior to sx; MD notified;
pt began influenza type sx: h/a, cough, sore throat, low grade temp, fatigue, inability to eat on 25OCT; 4NOV had lost approx 15 lbs-h/a (sever), muscle aches, weakness; trouble keeping eyes open;
LAB_DATA: dx viral syndrome; CBC-chem 20 monospot; spinal tap; CAT Scan  of head all normal;

SYMPTOM_TEXT: weakness, paresthesia in lt arm, h/a, body aches, fever, SOB & soreness in lt chest for 3 days, body chills;
OTHER_MEDS: pt recvd flu vax by Wyeth lot# 4938262 in lt deltoid;

SYMPTOM_TEXT: 22DEC93 mom reported that pt had a high pitched screaming for 4-5 hrs p/vax 20OCT93-t103;
3-4 days later a local reaction occurred around the site of vax; It was slightly erythematous area w/papules scattered throughout;
